1
00:00:32,740 --> 00:00:35,110
I'll go back.

2
00:00:35,110 --> 00:00:41,420
Back to where I originally came from.
Before it's too late.

3
00:00:42,890 --> 00:00:50,630
If perhaps... If I start planning on
liking you, you told me to tell you, right?

4
00:00:53,130 --> 00:00:56,540
It's been formed. A plan.

5
00:00:58,300 --> 00:01:02,970
So... Don't go.

6
00:01:12,150 --> 00:01:14,420
Don't go?

7
00:01:15,190 --> 00:01:16,860
Yes.

8
00:01:18,090 --> 00:01:19,830
Don't go.

9
00:01:21,890 --> 00:01:24,500
Now enough. Let's go home.

10
00:01:29,170 --> 00:01:33,570
Heo Joon Jae, what's the matter? Are you okay?

11
00:01:33,610 --> 00:01:37,840
Heo Joon Jae? Heo Joon Jae!

12
00:01:38,910 --> 00:01:43,220
Heo Joon Jae! Heo Joon Jae!

13
00:01:45,050 --> 00:01:49,650
Heo Joon Jae! Heo Joon Jae!

14
00:02:24,420 --> 00:02:28,460
Heo Joon Jae! Heo Joon Jae!

15
00:02:28,460 --> 00:02:31,030
Heo Joon Jae!

16
00:02:31,030 --> 00:02:33,130
Please help!

17
00:02:33,130 --> 00:02:35,000
Has something happened? What's going on?

18
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,230
Heo Joon Jae!

19
00:02:36,230 --> 00:02:37,370
What's the matter?

20
00:02:37,370 --> 00:02:39,400
Hello? Someone has collapsed here.

21
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:40,640
- Heo Joon Jae! - Please send a medic.

22
00:02:40,640 --> 00:02:42,110
Please send someone quickly!

23
00:02:42,110 --> 00:02:43,610
- Hello? - What should we do?

24
00:02:44,710 --> 00:02:48,050
- Who are you?  - Who are you?

25
00:02:49,180 --> 00:02:53,290
I am Dam Ryeong.

26
00:02:54,590 --> 00:02:59,060
If you are me in the next life,

27
00:02:59,060 --> 00:03:02,660
just remember these words again
after waking from this dream.

28
00:03:02,660 --> 00:03:05,700
Everything repeats itself.

29
00:03:05,700 --> 00:03:09,870
The fate in this world is
continuing in that world.

30
00:03:09,870 --> 00:03:12,440
It's the same way with ill-fate.

31
00:03:13,110 --> 00:03:17,340
Protect that woman

32
00:03:18,340 --> 00:03:20,380
against the dangerous person.

33
00:03:26,350 --> 00:03:28,690
- Heo Joon Jae. - Excuse me, are you okay?

34
00:03:28,690 --> 00:03:31,290
Can you see this? Can you see this?

35
00:03:31,290 --> 00:03:32,190
Heo Joon Jae!

36
00:03:32,190 --> 00:03:33,830
Are you okay?

37
00:03:33,830 --> 00:03:35,860
I am okay.

38
00:03:38,330 --> 00:03:40,230
I am okay.

39
00:03:40,230 --> 00:03:42,100
Are you okay?

40
00:03:43,770 --> 00:03:45,800
I'm okay.

41
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:18,270
The Legend of the Blue Sea

42
00:04:18,270 --> 00:04:19,600
Episode 9

43
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:21,840
Are you okay now?

44
00:04:21,840 --> 00:04:25,680
You. You also said you were in pain earlier.

45
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:29,210
I'm not in pain anymore.

46
00:04:33,250 --> 00:04:35,050
Why?

47
00:04:35,050 --> 00:04:39,830
While you were saying you love me or not, whether
I have plans to or not, and bothering me so much,

48
00:04:39,830 --> 00:04:43,730
were you thinking of running away from behind?

49
00:04:43,730 --> 00:04:47,230
Hey, you are scary.

50
00:04:48,930 --> 00:04:52,670
If you go, where? Who would you go to?

51
00:04:52,670 --> 00:04:54,870
That government employee?

52
00:04:54,870 --> 00:04:57,610
Jeong Hoon is gone now.

53
00:04:59,980 --> 00:05:03,480
Why? Where has he gone?

54
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:06,990
Far.

55
00:05:10,460 --> 00:05:13,190
Did you also plan to go after him far away?

56
00:05:13,190 --> 00:05:16,160
Why? Did he ask you to go far
away and eat ramyun with him?

57
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:19,600
It wasn't Jeong Hoon who cooked me ramyun.

58
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:23,300
Do you mean... he isn't that guy?

59
00:05:23,300 --> 00:05:25,500
Then who is that guy?

60
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:28,040
I can't tell you that.

61
00:05:31,740 --> 00:05:35,250
This won't do. You follow me.

62
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:41,850
- Look here. See,
there are lots of dolls, right?  -Yeah.

63
00:05:41,850 --> 00:05:43,560
Pick one.

64
00:05:44,460 --> 00:05:46,390
I choose that pink octopus.

65
00:05:46,390 --> 00:05:50,060
Okay, you chose the pink octopus, right?

66
00:05:50,060 --> 00:05:55,500
That's what you chose, so you have
to pick out that one no matter what.

67
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:57,970
Here, try it.

68
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:04,210
I did it!

69
00:06:07,980 --> 00:06:09,380
I almost did it, though.

70
00:06:09,380 --> 00:06:14,020
You're right, it almost came out, right? But it
didn't actually come all the way out, you know.

71
00:06:14,020 --> 00:06:19,120
Life is naturally all about something that
is about to work out but then it may not.

72
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:21,830
But if you give up here,

73
00:06:21,830 --> 00:06:27,130
then that pink octopus that you
chose will never be able to come out.

74
00:06:27,130 --> 00:06:28,700
Try it again.

75
00:06:44,520 --> 00:06:45,920
I guess it's not working.

76
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:49,120
You're trying to give up like that again?

77
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:53,060
If you decided on it,
you can't give up until it becomes yours.

78
00:06:53,060 --> 00:06:55,690
Whether that's the pink octopus,

79
00:06:58,030 --> 00:06:59,830
or anything.

80
00:07:00,570 --> 00:07:03,270
Then I'll try again one more time.

81
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:22,390
- Hey, now—  - Wait, stay there.

82
00:07:30,060 --> 00:07:32,160
Ah, it almost did it.

83
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:36,300
From what I see,
there's something wrong with the machine.

84
00:07:36,300 --> 00:07:40,010
It looks like they loosened the
claw on purpose. Let's just go.

85
00:07:40,010 --> 00:07:41,970
Then give up?

86
00:07:41,970 --> 00:07:47,080
No. This isn't giving up, this is stopping for a bit.

87
00:07:47,910 --> 00:07:49,350
Until next time?

88
00:07:49,350 --> 00:07:53,890
Of course. How are you so smart now?
It's been a while...

89
00:07:53,890 --> 00:07:59,990
Anyway, the important thing is that you
should never give up on what you've chosen.

90
00:07:59,990 --> 00:08:02,290
Should you give up, or shouldn't you?

91
00:08:02,290 --> 00:08:03,800
Shouldn't.

92
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,800
That's right.

93
00:08:06,900 --> 00:08:09,370
Would you like to go and eat
Hobbang (steamed bun with filling)?

94
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:21,880
Hey, I told you not to go, but you didn't listen to me.

95
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:23,320
Something serious almost happened!

96
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:24,650
I said I'm okay.

97
00:08:24,650 --> 00:08:27,620
Who on earth was it? Did you see his face?

98
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:32,590
I'm not sure.

99
00:08:32,590 --> 00:08:34,930
Anyone that comes to mind?

100
00:08:34,930 --> 00:08:38,400
Well, since we have so many enemies,

101
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:40,700
I can't narrow it down quickly.

102
00:08:40,700 --> 00:08:42,230
He was spotted by the police
patrolling Hoehyeon-dong,

103
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:44,600
- What is it?  - and the
chase began in broad daylight.

104
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:46,740
What?

105
00:08:46,740 --> 00:08:49,810
- It's that person.  - Police failed to
apprehend right in front of their eyes...

106
00:08:49,810 --> 00:08:51,610
It's that person?

107
00:08:51,610 --> 00:08:53,550
The escaped prisoner? Ma Dae Young?

108
00:08:53,550 --> 00:08:57,480
Yes, that's right. It's him.

109
00:08:57,480 --> 00:09:00,420
He took his hat off today.

110
00:09:00,420 --> 00:09:03,120
Cheong, do you remember him, too?

111
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:04,240
It's that person, right?

112
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:07,360
The one who was wearing the police uniform
and cap when it was raining before.

113
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:11,000
He wore a police cap and also a black cap.

114
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:15,900
You... Have you seen him after that day?

115
00:09:15,900 --> 00:09:17,840
Yes, when I was passing out the flyers.

116
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:23,810
Whoa! I am so shocked so many times.
Do you see the goosebumps?

117
00:09:23,810 --> 00:09:29,110
Then, the escapee was tailing our Cheong? Why?

118
00:09:29,110 --> 00:09:32,720
If something like that happened,
you should have told me!

119
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:34,920
Are you a fool?

120
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:40,130
Cheong wouldn't have known, either. You just
found out, too. Why are you blaming her?

121
00:09:46,530 --> 00:09:50,400
Ah, that punk.
He is just acting up for no good reason.

122
00:10:01,410 --> 00:10:05,250
Ah, it's cold. What are you doing there? Come on in.

123
00:10:07,790 --> 00:10:08,620
Have a seat.

124
00:10:08,620 --> 00:10:12,490
Why the heck would that jerk be tailing Cheong?

125
00:10:13,490 --> 00:10:17,030
Did he just follow Cheong?
He called you out and almost killed you.

126
00:10:17,030 --> 00:10:19,200
Something serious really
could have happened to you!

127
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:22,430
So, that's what I'm saying.
Why would that jerk follow Cheong...

128
00:10:22,430 --> 00:10:25,940
The fate in this world is
continuing in that world.

129
00:10:25,940 --> 00:10:28,640
It's the same way with ill-fate.

130
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:34,110
Protect that woman against
the dangerous person.

131
00:10:35,610 --> 00:10:37,050
Hyung.

132
00:10:37,050 --> 00:10:38,650
What?

133
00:10:40,650 --> 00:10:45,160
Don't take it the wrong way.

134
00:10:45,160 --> 00:10:48,760
- I had a dream.  - A dream?

135
00:10:48,760 --> 00:10:52,660
In that dream, I was living in the Joseon period.

136
00:10:52,660 --> 00:10:57,170
And I was wearing that bracelet.

137
00:10:57,170 --> 00:11:01,410
The bracelet? You mean Kim Dam Ryeong's bracelet?

138
00:11:02,410 --> 00:11:05,180
Ah, so you were Kim Dam Ryeong in the dream?

139
00:11:05,180 --> 00:11:06,480
Yes.

140
00:11:07,510 --> 00:11:09,650
I believe I was.

141
00:11:09,650 --> 00:11:11,140
It's possible.

142
00:11:11,140 --> 00:11:12,910
After seeing the movie
"The Admiral: Roaring Currents,"

143
00:11:12,910 --> 00:11:14,720
I had a dream where I was Admiral Yi in it.

144
00:11:14,720 --> 00:11:16,460
Aish, I'm not talking about
that kind of nonsense dream.

145
00:11:16,460 --> 00:11:19,660
Look who's talking. Your dream is the nonsense
one. How could you be Kim Dam Ryeong?

146
00:11:19,660 --> 00:11:21,290
Is it like you're looking back at your past life?

147
00:11:21,290 --> 00:11:26,900
It's not like it's my past life, but I feel
like I'm looking at a parallel universe.

148
00:11:28,130 --> 00:11:31,640
- Myself in another universe.
- You in another universe, my butt!

149
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:33,670
It's because I've been talking
to you about the bracelet,

150
00:11:33,670 --> 00:11:36,590
and Si Ah told you about
the excavation of the shipwreck.

151
00:11:36,590 --> 00:11:38,510
That's why you're having
this nonsense dream.

152
00:11:38,510 --> 00:11:40,730
The reality is governing your dream.
You're the one who studied neurosciences.

153
00:11:40,730 --> 00:11:43,720
How can you not realize it?

154
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:47,550
- Ah, is it like that? - Of course, it is.

155
00:11:47,550 --> 00:11:51,020
Ah. I've been kind of off recently.

156
00:11:51,020 --> 00:11:56,900
Hey. It's natural to have weird
dreams before your big projects.

157
00:11:56,900 --> 00:12:01,070
It must be a sign that our Project
Ahn Jin Joo will be a big success.

158
00:12:01,070 --> 00:12:02,570
Huh?

159
00:12:03,670 --> 00:12:06,610
Yes, that girl named Seo Yoo Na.

160
00:12:07,770 --> 00:12:13,080
It seems like that girl and my
Elizabeth had some troubles.

161
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:19,180
You know girls like that
always stand out in a poor way.

162
00:12:19,180 --> 00:12:22,420
Oh, my. Did you get a call from her mom? Why?

163
00:12:23,420 --> 00:12:25,590
She asked to have her included in our swim team?

164
00:12:26,460 --> 00:12:30,100
Well... Will you let her in?

165
00:12:30,930 --> 00:12:34,400
Of course not. That's right.

166
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:37,970
When there are kids like that in the
mix, it's always our kids who suffer.

167
00:12:37,970 --> 00:12:42,240
Of course, I trust you. Then...

168
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:45,940
Okay. Let's talk details when we meet.

169
00:12:45,940 --> 00:12:48,980
Okay, yes. Bye!

170
00:12:48,980 --> 00:12:53,450
You were on the phone for 1.5 hours
but you didn't discuss the details?

171
00:12:53,450 --> 00:12:54,690
Honey,

172
00:12:55,690 --> 00:12:58,290
did you get to talk to Chairman Heo?

173
00:12:58,290 --> 00:13:02,830
Well. I invited him to a dinner, but he
acts all busy and doesn't set up the time.

174
00:13:02,830 --> 00:13:05,700
Omo, I've been providing an endless
supply of banchan (side dishes) for him

175
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:08,170
since I was told he liked them.

176
00:13:08,170 --> 00:13:12,500
Is it like dine and dash? What's wrong with them?

177
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:14,560
He's not an easy guy.

178
00:13:14,560 --> 00:13:17,210
If there's anything of investment value,
he'd do that himself and won't give them to us.

179
00:13:17,210 --> 00:13:20,750
That's why we're trying this hard,

180
00:13:20,780 --> 00:13:24,650
so he can share some of them now, huh? Gracious.

181
00:13:25,850 --> 00:13:28,720
It's been so hard to put aside that secret fund.

182
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:30,600
I was so careful not to get
caught in the external audits

183
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:33,060
or by the National Tax Services.

184
00:13:33,060 --> 00:13:35,890
We saved it up by putting in our blood and sweat.

185
00:13:35,890 --> 00:13:38,700
Of course, we have. If you call this black money,

186
00:13:38,700 --> 00:13:42,300
I feel wronged. I worked very hard for that money!

187
00:13:42,300 --> 00:13:44,870
Preach, Honey!

188
00:13:44,870 --> 00:13:51,680
You've worked so hard.
We really will invest this money well

189
00:13:51,780 --> 00:13:56,280
and won't let your efforts go to waste.

190
00:13:56,280 --> 00:14:00,520
Yes, Honey. Let's give our best tonight as well!

191
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:02,590
Say what?

192
00:14:02,590 --> 00:14:06,360
- Who is it? - Korea Post.
Is Ms. Kang Seo Hee available?

193
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:10,830
It's court registered mail,
so she has to accept it herself.

194
00:14:16,170 --> 00:14:18,770
How dare you show up here. Are you crazy?

195
00:14:18,770 --> 00:14:22,140
It's not like I wanted to.
I am cold, hungry, and out of money.

196
00:14:28,580 --> 00:14:32,380
Heo Joon Jae is not an easy target.
He wiggles his way out every time.

197
00:14:32,380 --> 00:14:38,220
Chairman Heo is trying to set up meetings
with his lawyer to formalize his will.

198
00:14:38,220 --> 00:14:41,030
Will you get your senses back
after I've lost everything?

199
00:14:41,030 --> 00:14:45,530
What are we going to do if Chairman Heo goes to
meet Joon Jae and gives all his fortune to him?

200
00:14:47,370 --> 00:14:48,800
Hurry and leave now.

201
00:14:49,740 --> 00:14:52,070
- Sorry about the trouble at
this late hour.- No problem.

202
00:14:52,070 --> 00:14:53,770
Bye.

203
00:14:54,940 --> 00:14:56,240
Hi.

204
00:14:57,340 --> 00:14:59,440
Oh, Chi Hyeon.

205
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:02,080
Do they deliver at this late hour?

206
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:06,320
That's what I was wondering. He must be behind
his schedule due to the busy year-end season.

207
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:08,190
- Have you eaten? - Yes, I have.

208
00:15:08,190 --> 00:15:09,450
Let's go in.

209
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:12,790
Have you eaten, Mother?

210
00:15:14,490 --> 00:15:15,960
Let's go in.

211
00:15:20,030 --> 00:15:21,600
What is it?

212
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:25,370
Mother, did you hear about Joon Jae, by any chance?

213
00:15:25,370 --> 00:15:28,870
How would I know?

214
00:15:28,870 --> 00:15:32,010
I ran into him recently. By pure luck.

215
00:15:32,010 --> 00:15:33,980
Oh, you did?

216
00:15:35,180 --> 00:15:36,680
Did you tell your father?

217
00:15:36,680 --> 00:15:40,590
Of course not. I'm telling you first.

218
00:15:40,590 --> 00:15:45,860
Good job. He's been under stress
about a few things recently.

219
00:15:45,860 --> 00:15:48,790
I think it will be better that you
don't tell him that for a while.

220
00:15:48,790 --> 00:15:51,060
By any chance, do you know already?

221
00:15:52,060 --> 00:15:56,070
- What? - Where Joon Jae lives and how he is.

222
00:15:57,570 --> 00:15:59,540
I told you already that I don't know.

223
00:15:59,540 --> 00:16:05,540
Then why won't you ask me more about him?
Aren't you curious since I met him?

224
00:16:08,080 --> 00:16:13,350
Your father and I have huge
scars we got from Joon Jae.

225
00:16:13,390 --> 00:16:17,760
Wouldn't it be weird if I get all
interested when your father isn't?

226
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:23,100
Mother, what if Father
couldn't show his emotions

227
00:16:23,100 --> 00:16:26,400
because of the two of us?

228
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:30,970
I am also sorry that their
relationship went south,

229
00:16:30,970 --> 00:16:33,670
but I'm not sure if I'd like him to come back.

230
00:16:34,510 --> 00:16:38,340
Don't you like how things are right now?

231
00:16:38,340 --> 00:16:40,550
Do you think we'll keep how things
are right now when Joon Jae returns?

232
00:16:40,550 --> 00:16:43,480
- But I... - Yes, you.

233
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:47,620
Do you think you could keep all that you have now?

234
00:16:52,260 --> 00:16:57,760
Mother, I want to protect you.

235
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:02,970
My good son! However...

236
00:17:02,970 --> 00:17:07,470
That's my job, to protect us.

237
00:17:08,370 --> 00:17:10,280
Let's get in quickly.

238
00:17:19,580 --> 00:17:21,150
Yes. Bye.

239
00:17:31,900 --> 00:17:34,600
There's footage of him from the surveillance
camera from the nearby convenience store.

240
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:35,670
It's the back of him, though.

241
00:17:35,670 --> 00:17:39,810
He knows blind spots like nobody's business.

242
00:17:39,810 --> 00:17:42,370
That's why the police haven't
been able to catch him so far.

243
00:17:46,240 --> 00:17:47,780
Hello?

244
00:17:48,580 --> 00:17:51,250
010-3654-23

245
00:17:54,950 --> 00:17:56,690
Who is this?

246
00:17:56,690 --> 00:18:00,060
Hi, do you happen to know
Department Head Nam Seong Joon?

247
00:18:00,960 --> 00:18:04,130
Who is asking about him?

248
00:18:04,130 --> 00:18:05,960
