bastards who con even sicker bastards.

734
00:55:07,320 --> 00:55:09,990
Still, they're lying to people.

735
00:55:11,220 --> 00:55:15,790
Cheong, you've never done that?
Not once lied to people?

736
00:55:16,460 --> 00:55:19,660
You don't have any secrets you can't tell us?

737
00:55:19,660 --> 00:55:21,500
I feel like you do.

738
00:55:21,500 --> 00:55:25,600
Just stop! Why are you cornering her like that!

739
00:55:25,600 --> 00:55:28,170
What's this? Are you really the parent, or what?

740
00:55:28,170 --> 00:55:31,780
Tae Oh, isn't this weird!?
He's just completely sticking up for her!

741
00:55:31,780 --> 00:55:34,780
Between the two of you, is there a
change in your relationship or something?

742
00:55:34,780 --> 00:55:35,850
- No. - Yes.

743
00:55:35,850 --> 00:55:39,890
What?! What's the answer?! You said
yes and no!? What's the right answer!?

744
00:55:39,890 --> 00:55:42,850
Just be quiet! Don't chat in my car.

745
00:55:42,850 --> 00:55:44,960
If you're going to chat, then get off!

746
00:55:48,590 --> 00:55:51,960
Oh, Si Ah. Really?

747
00:55:53,500 --> 00:55:55,300
I'll be right there.

748
00:55:56,200 --> 00:55:58,470
Let me out. I have to go somewhere.

749
00:55:58,470 --> 00:56:00,440
You are really going to get out?
Where are you going?

750
00:56:00,440 --> 00:56:04,380
Si Ah said she has something to show me.

751
00:56:10,820 --> 00:56:14,520
I haven't seen it yet, either,
but the underclassman that excavated it

752
00:56:14,520 --> 00:56:16,390
says this one's really special.

753
00:56:16,390 --> 00:56:20,060
Typically, porcelains or paintings and
calligraphic works excavated from a house

754
00:56:20,060 --> 00:56:22,060
cannot be preserved in good condition.

755
00:56:22,060 --> 00:56:27,930
But this one—it was buried
in a completely sealed box.

756
00:56:27,930 --> 00:56:29,370
Buried?

757
00:56:29,370 --> 00:56:34,510
Yeah. As if, someone was asking
for it to be found in the future.

758
00:56:44,580 --> 00:56:47,620
- Wait a minute.- Hm?

759
00:56:47,620 --> 00:56:51,320
Can I look at it by myself for a minute?

760
00:56:52,660 --> 00:56:55,460
Ah, well, sure.

761
00:58:43,400 --> 00:58:45,900
Epilogue

762
00:58:45,900 --> 00:58:50,010
From now and to the full moon of the last
month of the year, there remain 19 days.

763
00:58:50,880 --> 00:58:55,280
What shall I do? What must I do

764
00:58:55,280 --> 00:58:58,620
for the person in my dream to believe me?

765
00:58:59,580 --> 00:59:01,420
What must I do?

766
00:59:04,290 --> 00:59:12,060
♬ Being under the same sky with you ♬

767
00:59:12,060 --> 00:59:15,630
I ask that you be meticulous.

768
00:59:15,670 --> 00:59:20,410
- Because it is a piece that must be
preserved for a long time.  - Yes.

769
00:59:20,410 --> 00:59:27,350
♬ If we can walk as far as the blue sea's horizon ♬

770
00:59:27,350 --> 00:59:35,150
♬ I won't let go of your hand. ♬

771
